The paper proposes a method for generating saliency maps for point-cloud data, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves assigning scores to individual points based on their contribution to the model's recognition loss, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves geometric operations on point-cloud data, which is a topic studied in computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) in the form of releasing code for experiments, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
